Chairman, Lobi Stars Foot­ball Club (FC), Engr Benson Abounu said that the state Governor Samuel Ortom has expressed confidence in the ability of the new manage­ment of the club to take Lobi out of relegation zone. Abounu, whoisalsotheState Deputy Governor disclosed this when he hosted the new man­agement and was introduced to the new coach, Baba Ganaru in his office on Friday. It would be recalled that Dominic Iorfa was appoint­ed the new Vice-Chairman of Lobi Stars earlier in the week, which was closely fol­lowed with the appointment of Ganaru as Head Coach on Thursday. Abounu pledged that Gov­ernor Ortom has assured him that he would give the team his maximum support. According to him, “He (Or­tom) expressed confidence in the person of Dominic Iorfa and his ability to take the team out of relegation. “It’s his belief that Iorfa can do the trick, hence he gave him (Iorfa) the go ahead to reposition the team and in turn achieve results and by this, take us out of the loom­ing shame that relegation will bring on us. “Your utmost task is that Lobi Stars will begin to find the back of the net and we are putting all our trust in you and will give you all the support it requires for you to succeed,” he stated. Abounu also assured the management that it would ensure that motivation pack­ages for players were put in place so that players can put in their best and deliver on their mandate. POLL He observed that “If play­ers are not motivated, they will not give you the desired results; players must bring on board extreme determi­nation, without which they would not get results.” While introducing Coach Ganaru, Iorfa explained that he decided to bring in a seasoned football coach like Ganaru to salvage the team, because of the circumstances the team has found itself. He assured Government on behalf of the new coach that the task given them would be achieved, adding that if anyone can do it, it was Ganaru.